race.comment: ACANTILADO (1) resumed at Swan Hill in the same race, beaten less than 1L. He is an improving galloper and positions forward. Strips fitter and has winning claims. SUPER NIC (5) resumed in good order and then placed second behind a dominant winner at Wagga. Finally draws a low barrier, and McDougall staying aboard is a decent push for his chances. He has to be entertained as well. SPIRITUAL STAR (4) is in Canberra's premier stable and wasn't too far away at the Sapphire Coast on debut. Has a senior jockey on today, and quick improvement wouldn't surprise. LAUNCH MODE (13) resumed with a good effort at Corowa and has to be included on the back of that effort.
